# Spec Kit Plans

**Spec Kit is the implementation authority.** All feature work must flow from spec kit; Cursor plans are strategic overlays that point to specs.

## Implementation Rule

Always implement from a Spec Kit spec → plan → tasks. Never implement from a Cursor plan or backlog item alone.

1. **Spec kit exists first** — Create `.specify/specs/<spec-name>/` with `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md` before implementing.
2. **Cursor plan links to spec kit** — Every Cursor plan must reference the spec kit path: "Implement per `.specify/specs/<spec-name>/`".
3. **Implementation follows tasks.md** — Execute tasks in order; use tasks as the checklist.
4. **Update tasks when done** — Check off completed tasks in `tasks.md` as work is finished.

## Required Output

Every plan that defines or implements a feature must produce a **spec kit** in `.specify/specs/<spec-name>/`:

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `spec.md` | Requirements, user stories, schema, acceptance criteria |
| `plan.md` | Implementation order, phases, file impacts |
| `tasks.md` | Granular, checkable tasks |

## When Making Cursor Plans

**Create the spec kit first.** When you create a Cursor plan for feature work:

1. Create `.specify/specs/<spec-name>/` with `spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md` before or alongside the plan
2. The Cursor plan MUST reference the spec kit: "Implement per `.specify/specs/<spec-name>/`"
3. The spec kit is the canonical artifact; the Cursor plan is a thin strategic overlay

Do not create Cursor plans that define features without a corresponding spec kit.

## When to Create Spec Kits

- New features or backlog items
- Emergent fixes that warrant documentation
- Any work that will be tracked in BACKLOG.md
- **Before or when creating a Cursor plan** — plans point to specs, not replace them

## Pre-Implementation Checklist

Before implementing any feature:

- [ ] Spec kit exists (spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md)
- [ ] Cursor plan links to spec kit path
- [ ] Implementation will follow tasks.md in order

After implementing:

- [ ] Completed tasks checked off in tasks.md
- [ ] If `prisma/schema.prisma` changed: migration folder committed; read [.agents/skills/prisma-migration-discipline/SKILL.md](../../.agents/skills/prisma-migration-discipline/SKILL.md) when unsure — **migrate deploy** is the production contract, not `db push` alone
- [ ] `npm run build` and `npm run check` pass
- [ ] **Human summary** — In the PR, ticket, or chat where you report the work, add a **short plain-language wrap-up** so anyone can understand without reading every file:
  - **What changed** (1–3 sentences)
  - **Why it matters** for players, stewards, or ops
  - **How to try it** (URLs, `npm run …`, seeds) when relevant
  - Optional **“like I’m five”** line: the idea in very simple words, no jargon  
  Technical diffs stay the source of truth; this is additive.

## Example

Planning "Daemons inner work collectibles" → create `.specify/specs/daemons-inner-work-collectibles/spec.md`, `plan.md`, `tasks.md`.

Do not create plans that only produce `.cursor/plans/*.plan.md` without corresponding spec kit files. The spec kit is the canonical artifact; the Cursor plan summarizes or links to it.
